        • m_fitnessValue

          double[] m_fitnessValue
          Stores the fitness value(s) of this Chromosome as determined by the active fitness function(s). A value of Double.NaN indicates that a fitness value has not yet been set.

        • m_performanceValue

          java.util.TreeMap<K,V> m_performanceValue
          Stores the performance value(s) of this Chromosome as determined by the active fitness function(s). A performance value is a measure of the performance of a Chromosome that is not used to determine the fitness of an individual in the evolutionary process. A value of Double.NaN indicates that a performance value has not yet been set.

        • m_overallFitnessValue

          double m_overallFitnessValue
          Stores the overall fitness value of this Chromosome, either as determined by the active fitness function or as determined by the NaturalSelector based on the fitness values over all objectives. A value of Double.NaN indicates that a fitness value has not yet been set.

          double crowdingDistance
          Used by selection algorithms to store a value representing how crowded the fitness space is relative to other individuals with the same rank (on the same Pareto front), most useful for multi-objective selection algorithms such as NSGA-II.

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_value

        • m_upperBounds

          int m_upperBounds
          The upper bounds of values represented by this Gene. If not explicitly provided by the user, this should be set to Integer.MAX_VALUE.

        • m_lowerBounds

          int m_lowerBounds
          The lower bounds of values represented by this Gene. If not explicitly provided by the user, this should be set to Integer.MIN_VALUE

        • m_boundsUnitsToIntegerUnits

          long m_boundsUnitsToIntegerUnits
          Stores the number of integer range units that a single bounds-range unit represents. For example, if the integer range is -2 billion to +2 billion and the bounds range is -1 billion to +1 billion, then each unit in the bounds range would map to 2 units in the integer range. The value of this variable would therefore be 2. This mapping unit is used to map illegal allele values that are outside of the bounds to legal allele values that are within the bounds.

          Configuration m_activeConfiguration
          The current active configuration that is in use.
